<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 05 at 4:59PM EDT until April 05 at 9:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A TORNADO WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 515 PM EDT FOR PORTIONS
OF HAMPTON...COLLETON AND ALLENDALE COUNTIES...
At 459 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm capable of producing a tornado
was located over Rivers Bridge State Park, moving northeast at 35
mph.
HAZARD...Tornado.
SOURCE...Radar indicated rotation.
IMPACT...Flying debris will be dangerous to those caught without
shelter. Mobile homes will be damaged or destroyed. Damage
to roofs, windows, and vehicles will occur.  Tree damage is
likely.
Locations impacted include:
Lodge and Ashton.
TORNADO...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN</description>
<instruction>Report damage directly to the Charleston National Weather Service at
888-383-2024 when it is safe to do so.</instruction>
